        section#research.research-section.bg-light.pb-5
            .container.px-4.px-lg-5.pb-5
                h2.text-center.text-uppercase.text-secondary.mb-4.pt-3 Research
                .row.mb-4#research-intro
                    p.col-12.text-center.m-auto Here is a list of papers related to Entalpic's research interests.
                    p.col-12.text-center.m-auto Some of them we are authors on, some others are just cool papers we like. Enjoy!
                .row.gx-4.gx-lg-5.justify-content-center
                    .col-lg-6.mb-4
                        .card
                            .card-body.entalpic-paper
                                h5.card-title
                                    a(href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2312.07511") A Hitchhiker's Guide to Geometric GNNs for 3D Atomic Systems
                                p.card-text.text-black-50
                                    | This paper provides a comprehensive overview of Geometric Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) for modeling 3D atomic systems, highlighting their architectures, applications, and future directions.
                    .col-lg-6.mb-4
                        .card
                            .card-body
                                h5.card-title
                                    a(href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2312.03687") MatterGen: a generative model for inorganic materials design
                                p.card-text.text-black-50
                                    | This paper introduces a diffusion-based generative model designed to create new inorganic materials by learning and leveraging patterns from existing material datasets.
                    .col-lg-6.mb-4
                        .card
                            .card-body
                                h5.card-title
                                    a(href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2010.09435") An Introduction to Electrocatalyst Design using Machine Learning for Renewable Energy Storage
                                p.card-text.text-black-50
                                    | This paper explores how machine learning techniques can be applied to design electrocatalysts, aiming to improve renewable energy storage solutions.
                    .col-lg-6.mb-4
                        .card
                            .card-body.entalpic-paper
                                h5.card-title
                                    a(href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.05577") FAENet: Frame Averaging Equivariant GNN for Materials Modeling
                                p.card-text.text-black-50
                                    | This paper presents a fast, simple and expressive Geometric Graph Neural Network that enforces euclidean symmetries via a data projection step instead of model-design equivariant constraints.
                    .col-lg-6.mb-4
                        .card
                            .card-body
                                h5.card-title
                                    a(href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2401.00096") A foundation model for atomistic materials chemistry
                                p.card-text.text-black-50
                                    | This paper introduces a single general-purpose ML model for atomistic materials chemistry, capable of running stable molecular dynamics on a diverse set of problems in the physical sciences.
                    .col-lg-6.mb-4
                        .card
                            .card-body
                                h5.card-title
                                    a(href="https://chemrxiv.org/engage/chemrxiv/article-details/65957d349138d231611ad8f7") Challenges in high-throughput inorganic material prediction and autonomous synthesis
                                p.card-text.text-black-50
                                    | This paper discusses problems that can arise in unsupervised materials discovery, and hope that by addressing these, autonomous materials discovery can be brought closer to reality.

